  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Chop your <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> into quarters</p><p>Add your <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a heatproof bowl, then cover the bowl with <strong>cling film</strong> and pierce a few holes in the top with a fork</p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave </strong>for 8-10 min or until the potatoes are fork-tender</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-3-1715249240316-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-3-1715249240316-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-3-1715249240316-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-3-1715249240316-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-3-1715249240316-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over medium-high heat</p><p>Pat your <strong>chicken thighs</strong> dry and season them generously on both sides with <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chicken thighs</strong>, skin-side down and cover with a piece of <strong>tin foil</strong>, then a smaller pan</p><p>Add a heavy weight (eg. several tins) to the top pan and cook for 12 min, checking occasionally, until the chicken skin is golden and crispy</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-3-1715249243496-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-3-1715249243496-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-3-1715249243496-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-3-1715249243496-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-3-1715249243496-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your<strong> lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper and roughly shred</p><p>Chop your<strong> heritage tomatoes </strong>in half</p><p>Once the potatoes are tender, remove the cling film and add a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Give the <strong>seasoned</strong> <strong>potatoes </strong>a good mix up, then set aside to cool down</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-3-1715249253177-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-3-1715249253177-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-3-1715249253177-x700.jpg",
